==English==
===Etymology 1===
Coined approx 1993; onomatopoeic and influenced by ''[[meep]]''.

====Noun====
{{en-noun|meef|meefs}}
#The [[cry]] of a [[mongoose]].

====Verb====
{{en-verb|meef|meefs|meefed|meefing}}
# Of a [[mongoose]], to make its [[cry]].
#:''The cat goes [[meow]], the cow goes [[moo]], and the mongoose goes '''meef'''.''
#To screw something up, or behave in an irritating or stupid fashion.
#:"If you're just going to '''meef''', get the hell out of here."
#:"Man, I '''meefed''' this definition good."

===Derived terms===
*[[meefy]]

===Etymology 2===
From German ''[[Mief]]'' (bad smell).

====Noun====
'''meef'''
# {{cattag|Slang}} term used in east Vancouver for undesirable person or situation
#*'''Usage note:''' Its overuse by various crews have made it a word much like ''[[smurf]]'', e.g "I '''meefed''' this '''meef''' right up!  '''MEEF'''!", "Yeah give me 1 order of Chicken '''Meefs'''," or "Call me later, i'm watching Star '''Meef'''".

===Etymology 3===
Coined from Eric Schlosser’s book “Fast Food Nation” in September of 2001 at Oberlin College, whereby the words meat and beef were combined.

====Noun====
#A [[grey]], food-like [[substance]] that tastes like neither [[beef]] or [[meat]].
#:"What’s that '''meef''' on your plate?"
#:"My favorite dish: [[eggs]], '''meef''', and [[cheese]]."  
#A pseudonym for [[marijuana]].
#:"I just bought some '''meef''' in Harlem!"''

====Exclamation====
#A state of euphoria or exaltation
#:"I just got laid last night, '''meef!'''."
#A Greeting or salutation
#:"'''Meef''', how are you?"

====Verb====
#To become stoned or high due to the effects of [[marijuana]].
#:"I just smoked a J, now I’m really '''meefed!'''
#To end up in a difficult spot due to external factors. 
#:"I got '''meefed''' by that quantum physics exam."
#:"I was in a bar fight last night and I got very '''meefed''' up!"

